dct_description_sm: This ArcGrid data layer represents a Bare Earth digital elevation model (DEM) for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2009. The spatial resolution of the dataset is 10 meters. The dataset was originally published by the Dane County Land Information Office and Fly Dane Partnership on March 26, 2010. [The Bare Earth DEM was developed from LAS points and breaklines collected from a LiDAR flight flown in the Spring and Fall of 2009, as part of the Fly Dane 2009-2010 Project. The DEM is a raster data set in ESRI GRID format with an X, Y, Z value located at the center of each 10 ft. by 10 ft. cell. The DEM was generated from a DTM meeting National Map Accuracy Standards.]
